text: Hi everyone! I'm Jeannette, a freelance writer based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. I started my career as a journalist, but started doing content marketing about 5 years ago when I launched my ecommerce store. Since selling the business, I've been exploring a bunch of different things – from bartending to healthcare. Most recently, I've been pursuing a Masters of Research program in Media, Languages and Cultures and now that I've submitted my dissertation, I'm looking to get back into content marketing again! Very excited to be here to learn and hopefully, contribute meaningfully.

text: Hi folks. My name is Jason Patterson. I'm a longtime B2B content marketer now freelancing. My strongest domains/industries are telecoms & networking, biopharm, and general tech. I've also written for automotive, logistics, manufacturing, martech, and a lot of other things. If it's B2B content, I can do it, very well. In terms of unique skills, I'm very good at adapting technical subjects for non-technical audiences. I can also take a product's list of features and group them into a few key selling points for maximum effect. I'm also better than almost anyone alive at creating B2B social media posts & content for brands; if you want to know how to get more people to read your content on LinkedIn, I'm your man. Check out my LinkedIn profile w/portfolio here:   <https://bit.ly/31o7FSg>
